lt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9N2EjkQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Hamill then responded to human excrement, Ben Shapiro, who took offense at the post.

(I think it is his middle finger)</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6bOj4G4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Herebychoice]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My craft: I design and make clothing for people with physical differences and disabilities.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/lVRyGiG</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Uxr2xEv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This delightfully Hobbity waistcoat is designed for people with fine motor impairments and digestive disorders. It looks like wool but it is a stretchy fleece and can be taken off over the head. It is sewn together at the buttonholes so that it moves and gives like it is actually buttoned closed. Because the vest is stretchy, it can change with your stomach needs over the course of the day.

Did you know that some of us have stomach disorders that cause our waist sizes to change by 4 in in the course of just one hour? That can make it so that clothing that zips up becomes an agonizing prison very quickly.

This skirt is a very twirly full circle skirt with a hidden placket in the back that allows you to adjust it to whatever your waist size is in the moment. This is great for people who have stomach cancer, ulcers, diverticulitis, ibs, and crohn's. It's also great for people recovering from eating disorders who need clothing that doesn't force them to check in with their weight everyday.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gFyQB4N.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is a shot of the back placket that allows for the adjustability. Different skirt through. This beauty is fully lined wool.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fNz74IV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is a full circle skirt and it features a different kind of adjustable back. The back is made with extra fabric that can be gathered into a bunch or pleats to give the effect of a Victorian walking skirt. Because I'm all about that drama.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9mGzddO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This dress is made out of double brush knit which is one of the softest fabrics known to man. It has cute little puff sleeves, but it's also nice and stretchy so that it can move with your stomach, and is very gentle on the sensory needs. It's also a pullover, making it ideal for people with fine motor difficulties.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/witPEeC.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I started designing clothing for my stomach disorder out of necessity. I started doing it professionally when I realized how many people could benefit from adaptive clothing, but either had no idea it existed, or were turned off by how depressingly bland the options were. Why do the designers of adaptive clothing think that disabled people want to dress like boring white people in Olive garden commercials? We want personality, verve, expression!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4ctiY0z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Each item is made to your custom measurements. Are you at 6'5 and you've never actually had a floor-length skirt touch the floor? I can help. Are you 4 ft 6 and never had a maxi dress that didn't try to swallow you whole? I've got you.

This dress is a pullover and made out of sensory friendly flannel. It's great for people with stomach difficulties because it is cut in the swing style, so you can belt it for a fitted look or wear it loose for maximum comfort. Belted styles are also great for people recovering from eating disorders because you just pull it on, tie your belt and go.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EiVt4wI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Overalls are the most comfortable clothing on Earth and I don't understand why we don't all wear them all the time.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gAIt0QO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is my pinafore apron worn over one of the other dresses. Because everything I make has to have massive pockets.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UObLx1e.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This pinafore dress is my favorite cottage core look. It is very comfortable with its adjustable waistband in the back and flat waistband in the front and oh so cute. I specifically designed cottage core, goblin core, and dark academia clothing so that people with disabilities can have exciting options.

If you like what you see, feel free to follow me on Facebook and Instagram @eightfoldfox and check out my website at www.eightfoldfox.com.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/lVRyGiG</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[EightfoldFox]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The price of “Freedumb” in America.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7VTefsZ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/iFROPD6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VZwiv3x.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sauce: https://www.politicususa.com/2022/03/09/marjorie-taylor-greene-crushed-as-judge-rules-for-pelosi-on-mask-mandate.html</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/7VTefsZ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[BluesFish]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Time flies..</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/a7Llb5l</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IUVRg5X.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Lily and Chloe on YouTube:

https://youtube.com/user/KAftC</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/a7Llb5l</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Zergcollective]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>He is a professional</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/RDKOAtY</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/V72JivU.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/RDKOAtY</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Capinron]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Let them see</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/TaLG1T1</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/E2TWKIg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/TaLG1T1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PrettyFlyForALaowai]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Just ugh.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/eZy0XXI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ajXbpfP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>So I've been having a really nice time getting to know this young lady, and things seemed to be going quite well. But then the word policing began...

I said "things are kinda crazy at work."

Apparently, crazy is a bad word because it's offensive to the neurodivergent, and I'm not allowed to use it regardless of the context having nothing to do with it being used as a slight against anyone.

I said "I appreciate a partner who is intelligent and capable."

Apparently, capable is a bad word because it's offensive to the disabled, and I'm not allowed to use it regardless of the context having nothing to do with it being used as a slight against anyone.

There were more like this, and it just got to the point where it's so exhausting trying to police completely innocent words that I just can't be fucking bothered dealing with this person. I understand that certain words can be harmful, and I try my best to be considerate and thoughtful, but for fucks sakes, relax, lady. 

Yeesh.

* Update, since so many folks were asking for one. I tried to reach out and talk to her about it this morning and it turns out she has me muted and blocked on the app where we met, as well as texts. Not very satisfying for y'all I know, but there's nothing much I can do about it.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/eZy0XXI</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[HomeDepotAisle15]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Lots of good reason to stay home and work.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/lLebgKx</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ODUBA5i.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kRq7tvg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/lLebgKx</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lanhdanan]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Sorry Belgium</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Uu5mgLK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PdwsZ7D.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Uu5mgLK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[NomDeDieuDePutainDeBordelDeSaloperieDeMerde]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>How'd that work out for you ?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/TuUr9rv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jKOyTEW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/TuUr9rv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[naturi5mMeep52]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Surprising her Father with a visit after not seeing each other for over 3 years. She planned it 7 months ahead without telling him.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/GYx1aKQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KhXlXtt.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></descrip