ight: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FA7Al8z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eQr5GLS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PlmUyYL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dX4KvD8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ISsm54q.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QIUy1ej.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZwEhdYt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/68DDuLZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eNpYUnd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KUxsPfa</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[EzoDave]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>And then the murders began...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/LgKtE1D</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aySzWfH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://inkican.com/mesh</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/LgKtE1D</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[inkican]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Taking an overnight train from Chicago to New York</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/DvShJBg</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FQz7Ruk.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Story time! I was in Chicago today for a business trip with my favorite partners when my buddy tells me there’s a “bomb cyclone” winter storm coming to the area and our flights back east the next day might be delayed. Terrible thoughts of missing the weekend with my family cross my mind until another friend suggests a sleeper car on Amtrak. Turns out there an overnight train from Chicago to New York that takes a dozen hours, and after checking the Amtrak website, I found a nice option  - a one bedroom compartment with private bathroom and shower in your suite! Who knew!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zw1LoAN.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It was expensive ($1200!) but I could get a refund on my hotel room and flight and actually make it home instead of being stuck waiting for canceled flights or, worse, driving through a winter storm even airplanes won’t fly through. So I pulled the trigger and visions of the orient express danced in my head while sharing my excitement with my business partners over dinner. I had to leave dinner early to make sure I was on time for the train, but the restaurant was kind enough to wrap up my dinner to go so I could enjoy it in my one bedroom suite before bed. 

Here are some little known facts about my trip:</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IasDgBx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>- A one-bedroom compartment with an in-suite bathroom isn’t all it’s cracked up to be. I’m sure the residual moisture on the floor was cleaning solution. But could also be toilet water. I’m not going to investigate further.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TS3AB4x.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>- It was definitely a bad idea to bring my leftover dinner onto the train with me.  No mini fridge. Duh. I guess I wasn’t thinking but now my room smells like steak. I think it will be a different smell in the morning after sitting at room temperature all night.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sy3F4uU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>- The train was warmer than I thought it would be on a cold March night in Chicago. I found a thermostat thingie but I learned the dial is about as helpful as pushing an elevator button 7 times when it’s already lit. (Probably just there to make you feel better. )</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ClXs8mJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>- Before going to bed, it’s fun to check under your the seats for freebies from the last guest. I won a free pair of used underwear playing that game!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oz1A5nU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>- The bench seat turns into a bed.  Nice feature. Turns out the upper bunk is hidden away and released with a lever, so when you turn it, the top bunk comes down and reveals a 3” mattress already adorned with clean sheets and pillows. You just take the mattress/sheet combo and put it on the flattened bench seat and - presto! - a nice bed. More comfortable than it sounds, actually.  A solid 5/7.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EHNN7jG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>- One little gripe, perhaps: if you’re taller than 5’9”, your feet will touch the wall when laying down.  I am now wondering how many other feet I’m now foot-cousins with.  I decided to wear my socks to bed.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/piV4mEU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>- I’m pretty sure the people in the one bedroom suite next to mine have gas. Either that or the leftovers are starting to turn. There’s a helpful 1” gap under the door between our rooms so I can’t tell which. 

- I think there’s a 40% chance my locked compartment door will open on its own due to the train motion at some point during the night. And because I didn’t pack pajamas, I can’t help but think someone is going to be tapping my shoulder while I’m sleeping half naked and darth vadering through my CPAP mask, jumpstarting my consciousness like a taser on a sheep’s rear-end.  Should make for interesting dreams. 

Will I make it back to my home state? I’ll update tomorrow with the latest.

——

Morning update! https://imgur.com/gallery/GmNYl00</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/DvShJBg</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[jeffv2718]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Corporations always want it both ways</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ysKFzKm</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WIXDoMF.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ysKFzKm</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lanhdanan]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Mini dump!!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/0gFVzaQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kXt8YEs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/04NDjo6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3EGfKOM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/q2gfNMs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IYnS9Oq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/A3qKaWF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kbnDfqO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HC2M632.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lgquyfd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bUFA2Qk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hWF5Zke.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img a